SO MANY people ask me about ADHD…is so common. NHS waiting lists are intense and private is costly. Learning about it, reading and listening to tedx talks and podcasts on ADHD really are helpful in understanding yourself and a help alleviate life long frustration. https://t.co/Tr1sSWW1bZ

1st, I read tons about it. Try @ADDitudeMag .Then, I typed ‘ADULT ADHD’ in a box on this site https://t.co/0Kw8fnIx4u and found my amazing therapist. CHANGED MY LIFE. After a few months, I got formal diagnosis from psychiatrist and prescribed Elvanse. That and running REALLY help https://t.co/0BQJkwvFMh

I spent YEARS in 12 step programmes for bulimia. I stopped all bitching and gossiping as is the way of the programme. Turns out, bulimia was symptom of ADHD and now I have treatment for it, bulimia no longer rules me! I can be a cow again and this is sweet freedom #blessed
@Lachlan_Edi Anyway. Come to my current show…way funnier! And have a drink at the bar to chat. I find all this interesting but too time consuming to do on twitter

@Lachlan_Edi Hello again! Yes twitter is hard to explain things.. I just don’t connect with comics whose shtick depends entirely on goading people to have endless conversations about ‘offence’ and how other people should/shouldn’t be feeling. Horse for courses but I don’t find joy in it.

@Lachlan_Edi Looking back on that bit…I put barely any thought into my shows back then. (I was a heartbroken drunk tbh) Anyway…It mattered to me that trans people we upset by that bit. It wasn’t manufactured. No more than me being upset at racist jokes when I was young. So i stopped it.

@Lachlan_Edi Firstly, thanks for coming to my show. I’d like to talk about this..did people manufacture offence to that bit?The letter I got from the mother of a trans girl in my audience was very heartfelt, and angry.I still doubled down, though ‘how can anyone be offended by ME??’
